==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bloodhound
<hw>Blood"hound`</hw> <pr>(bl⟦ucr⟧d"hound`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
breed of large and powerful dogs, with long, smooth, and pendulous ears,
and remarkable for acuteness of smell. It is employed to recover game or
prey which has escaped wounded from a hunter, and for tracking
criminals. Formerly it was used for pursuing runaway slaves. Other
varieties of dog are often used for the same purpose and go by the same
name. The Cuban bloodhound is said to be a variety of the
mastiff.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bloodied</ent>⟦br⟧
